body:
### Component

Forge

### Describe the feature you would like

Currently when I try to import a specific .sol file from a remote address I get errors:

```
//SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense
pragma solidity >=0.8.13;

import "https://gist.githubusercontent.com/JofArnold/bf2c4a094fcdd4aee2f52983c7714de8/raw/f8ca925324b3bf53354c84d47d080e6a87439233/BoredApeYachtClub.sol";

// TODO: Implement all user stories and one of the feature request
contract Game {
    uint256 public x;

    constructor() {
        x = 4;
    }
}

```

```
Compiler run failed:
Error (6275): Source "https://gist.githubusercontent.com/JofArnold/bf2c4a094fcdd4aee2f52983c7714de8/raw/f8ca925324b3bf53354c84d47d080e6a87439233/BoredApeYachtClub.sol" not found: File not found. Searched the following locations: "/home/ubuntu/solidity-exercise".
```

It treats the remote address like a local import.

Same code works in Remix, as well as with Hardhat/Truffle.

I may be mistaken, please let me know if there's any workaround for this.

